[{"Id": 1013625, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": "He was a devout and loyal companion of Imam Ali (a.s), from Iranian origin. After Imam Ali (a.s) purchased him and freed him from slavery, he became a date seller and therefore the title ’al-Tammar’. Imam Ali (a.s) taught him many branches of knowledge, including ilm-e-Manaya wal Balaya (esoteric knowledge of future events) and ilm-e-Taweel (interpretation and exegesis of the Qur’an). Imam Ali (a.s) would take him to a nearby desert in the middle of the night to teach him about future affairs/matters/events. Imam Ali (a.s) showed him the tree on which he would be hung till death and Misam used to pray by that tree and talk with it. But even as they hung him, he wouldn’t stop praising the Ahle Bayt (a.s) or stop mentioning the evil conduct of Bani Umayyah. So, Ibn Ziyad ordered his men to cut off his tongue and finally his body was left hanging for a few days.", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": null, "UrduDescription": null, "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSign7": null, "ArabicRedSign7": null, "ArabicBlueSign7": null, "ArabicText8": null, "ArabicGreenSign8": null, "ArabicRedSign8": null, "ArabicBlueSign8": null, "ArabicText9": null, "ArabicGreenSig